  {
    icon: '📱',
    title: 'Professional Business Number',
    text: "AI SMS runs on your business number. Developer programmes, specification discussions, and plumbing merchant orders stay separated from personal texts."
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How does the AI handle an inbound plumbing text?",
    answer: "Each text generates a branded response in your company name within seconds. A main contractor's programme text — 'first fix plots 14-17 starting Wednesday, copper carcass, SVPs both sides, PEX UFH ground floor, need your gang 7am' — is confirmed with the plot range, pipe system, SVP locations, UFH, and start time preserved. A homeowner's enquiry — 'dripping tap in the bathroom, can you come and fix it?' — receives a response asking about the tap type, whether it is hot or cold side, and the preferred visit day."
  },
  {
    question: "Will callers recognise the AI?",
    answer: "The response reads like a plumber checking messages between joints — system-specific, fixture-aware, and practically focused. It references pipe types, cylinder models, sanitaryware brands, and programme schedules. Main contractors texting first-fix requirements expect a knowledgeable reply that confirms system capability and gang numbers."
  },
  {
    question: "How does it handle existing client texts?",
    answer: "Regular developer clients text programme changes — 'plot 15 delayed, plasterer not finished, push first fix to Thursday' or 'add an extra WC to the downstairs cloakroom on plot 18.' The AI captures every amendment and separates programme updates from new business enquiries on your dashboard."
  },
  {
    question: "What does AI SMS cost for plumbing contractors?",
    answer: `AI SMS is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as a channel add-on. A bathroom renovation generates £3,000 to £10,000. Confirming one developer's Monday first-fix start — while you soldered a supply riser in a bathroom on another site — locks in a week of programme revenue that far exceeds the annual channel cost.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I text back myself when I choose?",
    answer: "Post one reply and the AI steps back from that thread permanently. During measurement days and quoting sessions — handle texts directly. During active plumbing — when the blow torch is lit, the press gun is clamped, or the PEX is being routed through joists — let the AI manage the incoming commercial messages."
  },
  {
    question: "How is text data from plumbing enquiries stored?",
    answer: "Text messages containing property addresses, system specifications, developer schedule details, fixture selections, and contact information are encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Data goes only to you. Nothing is shared with competing plumbing firms or used for any secondary purpose."
  }
